def load_livestock_ts(
    columns:list=None, # Subset of ``['sheep', 'cattle', 'pigs']``. Returns all if None.
)-&gt;pd.DataFrame: # DatetimeIndex (annual frequency, year-start), requested columns.

Annual livestock counts in Australia from 1970 to 2007 (38 observations).
Three co-evolving animal population series — sheep, cattle, and pigs — that share common long-run drivers (rainfall, feed prices, land use). A clean, compact multivariate benchmark with no missing values.
This dataset is fully hardcoded — no internet connection required. Values are in millions of head, from the Australian Bureau of Statistics.

